	<refnamediv>
		<refname>ipfixcol-unirec-output</refname>
		<refpurpose>UniRec output plugin for IPFIXcol.</refpurpose>
	</refnamediv>
	
	<refsect1>
		<title>Description</title>
		<simpara>
			The <command>ipfix-unirec-output</command> plugin is an optional part of IPFIXcol (IPFIX collector) framework.
		</simpara>
	</refsect1>

	<refsect1>
		<title>Configuration</title>
		<simpara>There are two configuration XML files for ipfixcol that affects plugin usage.
		First one is internal configuration XML (<filename>/etc/ipfixcol/internalcfg.xml</filename>) where are list of all available plugins for the collecor. 
		UniRec plugin must be specified here to be usable.
		</simpara>
		<simpara><filename>internalcfg.xml</filename> unirec example</simpara>
		<programlisting>
	<![CDATA[
	<storagePlugin>
		<fileFormat>unirec</fileFormat>
		<file>/usr/share/ipfixcol/plugins/ipfixcol-unirec-output.so</file>
		<threadName>unirec</threadName>
	</storagePlugin>
	]]>
		</programlisting>
		<para></para>
		
		<simpara>The collector must be configured to use unirec output plugin in startup.xml configuration (<filename>/etc/ipfixcol/startup.xml</filename>). 
		The configuration specifies which plugins (destinations) are used by the collector to store data and provides configuration for the plugins themselves. 
		</simpara>
		<simpara><filename>startup.xml</filename> unirec example</simpara>
		<programlisting>
	<![CDATA[
	<destination>
		<name>make unirec from the flow data</name>
		<fileWriter>
			<fileFormat>unirec</fileFormat>
			<IPProtocol>4</IPProtocol>
			<remoteIPAddress>localhost</remoteIPAddress>
			<remotePort>3000</remotePort>
			<timeout>60</timeout>
			<format>SRC_IP;DST_IP;SRC_PORT;DST_PORT;PROTO;?TCP_FLAGS;?URL</format>
		</fileWriter>
	</destination>
	]]>
		</programlisting>
	
		<para>
			<variablelist>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>fileFormat</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>Same as in <filename>internalcfg.xml</filename> file.</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>IPProto</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>IP protocol to use. Possible values are 4, 6 and 64 (6 with IPv4 address mapping).</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>remoteIPAddress</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>IP address or hostname of remote site.</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>remoteIPAddress</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>IP address or hostname of the remote site.</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>remotePort</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>TCP port of the remote site.</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>timeout</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>Timeout before next reconnection attempt.</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term><command>format</command></term>
					<listitem>
						<simpara>UniRec format specification of the export format.</simpara>
					</listitem>
				</varlistentry>
			</variablelist>
		</para>
	</refsect1>

